{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it could have been that the rumor came-- often the Germans planted rumors, you know, in order to, you know, frighten people and then do whatever they wanted to do,",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know whether it was a real threat, or whether it wasn't, but I know that's the last time I was in a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think anybody went to the synagogue anymore after that, because very soon afterwards, the-- there was a law that by-- by a certain time, we had-- the Jews had to leave the provinces.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You no longer were allowed to live outside of the big cities.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The provinces were anything outside Amsterdam or The Hague.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, Holland is 11 provinces, you know, that's-- that's-- and we we not allowed to live there anymore.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now this was the end of '42 beginning of '43 when this came, OK?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- so my uncle, who had a big problem because he had to take care-- asides from his own family, he had to take care of two of us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then he had this mother-in-law from his first wife living with him, OK?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's my-- my older cousin's grandmother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her name was Maita Woresack, and she was living there also.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then there were three aunts also who were related to his-- not-- they were-- were not my aunts.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't even remember their name, but they were living nearby.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were related to-- to-- to him through his first wife, and he was taking care of them too.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Basically, he was paying for-- then for them to live with neighbors, but their food-- my aunt had to cook it for them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember I used to take-- that-- that's what I knew about that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I used to take them their food.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
